subSubSection.paragraph:
POSTERIOR GONOPODS (
Figs 124
D, 125B–D). Coxites (
c
) divided. Telopodites (
t
) present on posterolateral side, hairless, simple, but relatively massive. Coxal processes (
cp
) hook-shaped, curved anteriorly. Coxal vesicles (
cv
) present on anterior side.
